<title type="html"><![CDATA[10/21(Thu.) Inflation / Addiction (Host: Sherry Liao)]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://www.royalclub.tw/bbs3/viewtopic.php?t=551&amp;p=574#p574"><![CDATA[
21 October 2021(Thu.) Inflation / Addiction (Host: Sherry Liao)<br /><br />Agenda:<br />7:00-7:05 pm Opening Remarks<br />7:05-7:40 pm Session 1: Group Discussion<br />7:40-8:00 pm Individual Presentation<br />8:00-8:05 pm Break<br />8:05-8:40: Session 2: Group Discussion<br />8:40-9:00 pm Individual Presentation<br /><br /><span style="color: #BF0000">We will hold a <span style="font-weight: bold">hybrid meeting</span> on October 21 (Thursday):</span><br /><br /><span style="font-weight: bold">On-site meeting:</span><br />If you have received at least one dose of vaccine, please join our physical meeting: <br /><span style="text-decoration: underline">Dante coffee 丹堤 臺北市大安區濟南路3段25號 忠孝新生MRT Exit 3 or 6</span><br /><br /><span style="font-weight: bold">On-line meeting:</span><br />If you haven’t gotten any vaccine or live far away from Taipei, please join our online meeting:<br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="https://zoomtw.zoom.us/j/92987266213?pw">https://zoomtw.zoom.us/j/92987266213?pw</a><!-- m --> ... 09#success<br />Meeting ID:929 8726 6213<br />Password:112233<br /><br /><br /><span style="font-weight: bold">Session 1</span><br /><br />Higher inflation squeezing U.S. consumers as food prices, rents accelerate<br /><br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="https://www.reuters.com/world/us/us-consumer-prices-increase-solidly-september-2021-10-13/">https://www.reuters.com/world/us/us-con ... 021-10-13/</a><!-- m --><br /><br />1.      Do you think the cost of living has increased over the last few years?  Do you think the prices are still on the rise?<br /><br />2.      In your opinion, what consumer products are getting more expensive?  What are getting cheaper?<br /><br />3.      Does raising minimum wage increase cost of living?  What are the pros and cons of raising the minimum wage?<br /><br />4.      Federal Reserve Chair Jerome Powell asserted that high inflation is transitory.  What do you think?<br /><br />5.      What are the main causes of inflation? Who benefits from it?<br /><br /><br /><span style="font-weight: bold">Session 2</span><br /><br />China to ban kids from playing online games for more than three hours per week<br /><br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="https://www.cnbc.com/2021/08/30/china-to-ban-kids-from-playing-online-games-for-more-than-three-hours-per-week.html">https://www.cnbc.com/2021/08/30/china-t ... -week.html</a><!-- m --><br /><br />1.      Do you support the rules by Chinese government to cut children's online gaming time?  Do you think we should have similar rules in Taiwan?<br /><br />2.      If you are a parent, would you limit your kids’ video game-playing time?  What other limits would you give to your kids?<br /><br />3.      Do you agree with Chinese state media that online game is “opium” and should be restricted to prevent addiction?<br /><br />4.      In your opinion, what things and activities can people become addicted to? Should governments ban or restrict these addictions?<br /><br />5.      Do you think some people are more vulnerable to addiction than others?  What are the traits of an addictive personality?<br /><br /><br />P.S.<br />1.丹堤咖啡有100元低消喔!<br />2.參加三次(含實體及線上會議)後，只要繳交1,000元(學生500元)，即可成為ROYAL終身會員!<br />3.請帶著開放與熱情來參加全英文會話聚會!<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.royalclub.tw/bbs3/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=37037">JuliaHo</a> — Sat Oct 16, 2021 12:29 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
